{"bookId": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "moduleId": "689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08", "subjectId": "689477a745ed867065047092", "chapterId": "6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9", "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "count": 40, "questions": [{"id": 300080, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "Which among the following reactions represents Carbylamines reaction?", "options": ["$\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NH}_2+\\mathrm{CHCl}_3+3 \\mathrm{KOH} \\underset{\\text { alc }}{\\stackrel{\\Delta}{\\longrightarrow}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NC}+3 \\mathrm{KCl}+3 \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}$", "$\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NH}_2+\\mathrm{NHO}_2 \\stackrel{\\text { (i) } \\mathrm{NaNO}_2+\\mathrm{HCl}}{\\longrightarrow} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{OH}+\\mathrm{N}_2 \\uparrow+\\mathrm{HCl}$", "$\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NH}_2+\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COCl} \\stackrel{\\text { pyridine }}{\\longrightarrow} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NH}-\\mathrm{COCH}_3+\\mathrm{CHl}$", "$\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NH}_2+\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{X} \\rightarrow \\mathrm{R}_4 \\stackrel{+}{\\mathrm{N}} \\overline{\\mathrm{X}}+2 \\mathrm{HX}$"], "answer": 0, "solution": "$\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NH}_2+\\mathrm{CHCl}_3+3 \\mathrm{KOH} \\underset{\\text { alc }}{\\stackrel{\\Delta}{\\longrightarrow}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{NC}+3 \\mathrm{KCl}+3 \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}$\r\nCarbylamine reaction", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300081, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "The structure of the compound formed, when nitrobenzene is reduced by lithium aluminium hydride $\\left(\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4\\right)$ is", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-fdb6ba0312ec8453.png\"/><br/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7ff8aee1d9349930.png\"/><br/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-e408a0c492b37173.png\"/><br/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-2ac84f243116af0a.png\"/><br/>"], "answer": 2, "solution": "Nitrobenzene on reduction with lithium aluminium hydride $\\left(\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4\\right)$ gives azobenzene.\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7dbc6c664fefb0cc.png\"/><br/>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300082, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "The major product of the reaction is <img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-49188693e5a59459.png\" style=\"width:1.94653in;height:1.03333in\"/>", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-6c46e84e2a3089f2.png\" style=\"width:1.36667in;height:1.08681in\"/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-47fa9645010959f2.png\" style=\"width:1.44028in;height:1.05347in\"/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-51a696c28b400551.png\" style=\"width:1.37361in;height:1.1in\"/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-bb96c40dfd234929.png\" style=\"width:1.61319in;height:0.94653in\"/>"], "answer": 2, "solution": "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-515b20a08de7fc99.png\" style=\"width:5.84167in;height:1.29167in\"/>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300083, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "<p>In the reaction,</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-e4f8d60e64ce299c.png\" style=\"width: 357px; height: 122px;\" /></p><p>the product <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi></math> is _______.</p>", "options": ["<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-92040c17779b81cf.png\" style=\"width: 65px; height: 118px;\" />", "<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-5f6ee60c65e0ffc1.png\" style=\"width: 143px; height: 46px;\" />", "<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-a8c16eaa658de4ec.png\" style=\"width: 46px; height: 118px;\" />", "<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-4d766c4aeae8d251.png\" style=\"width: 46px; height: 84px;\" />"], "answer": 2, "solution": "<blockquote><p>It is an example of nucleophilic aromatic substitution reaction in which diazonium salts are formed as an intermediate and then the substitution takes place by cyanide ion, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> gas gets liberated. We obtain <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo></math> methyl benzonitrile as a significant product.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-a6f5f5c995351907.png\" style=\"width: 46px; height: 118px;\" /></p></blockquote>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300084, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "$\\mathrm{X}$ and $\\mathrm{Y}$ (major products) in the following reaction sequence are\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-99443bfb9b9b8081.png\"><br>", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-3790576164d46167.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-8979a191431fa1b7.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-f83c1fd2ca83e791.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-15070c23cd7986c2.png\"><br>"], "answer": 3, "solution": "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-faea9f6589d2f0b7.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300085, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "Identify $X$ and $Y$ of the following reaction sequence.\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-2966c57cc8e17480.png\"><br>", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-b440ab258786971c.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7d5154855f04b80d.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-2cd80a302705a71c.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-5cd255cf5ccec8e7.png\"><br>"], "answer": 3, "solution": "The complete reaction is as follows\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-cdbeab2879a29171.png\"><br><img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-a1a368a649ec16e6.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300086, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "Which of the following is a Gattermann reaction?", "options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>Ar</mo><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></msubsup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><msub><mi>HBF</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mover><msubsup><mi>ArN</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></msubsup><msubsup><mi>BF</mi><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo></msubsup><mo>&#10230;</mo><mi>ArF</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8593;</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>BF</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>", "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>Ar</mo><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></msubsup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mfrac><mi>KI</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi></mfrac><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>ArI</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8593;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>KX</mi></math>", "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>Ar</mo><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></msubsup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><mi>Cu</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HBr</mi></mrow></mover><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mi>ArBr</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8593;</mo></math>", "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>Ar</mo><msubsup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></msubsup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><mi>CuCl</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></mrow></mover><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mi>ArCl</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8593;</mo></math>"], "answer": 2, "solution": "<p>In this reaction benzenediazonium chloride is attacked by nucleophile eg. bromide ion here to remove nitrogen gas, as shown below:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>ArN</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></msubsup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><mi>Cu</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HBr</mi></mrow></mover><mi>ArBr</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300087, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "The major products $P$ and $Q$ in the following reactions are\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-f958d4ee98f79a46.png\"><br>\r\n$\\begin{array}{ll}P & Q\\end{array}$", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-9a483cba8d64c216.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-17f9188183ab6227.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-9cdbf8fbe9718deb.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-6559a8151065ed4a.png\"><br>"], "answer": 0, "solution": "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7ef4c682c880ed66.png\"><br><img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-64d35c33bf75488c.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300088, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "On heating benzyl amine with chloroform and ethanolic KOH, product obtained is", "options": ["benzyl alcohol", "benzaldehyde", "benzonitrile", "benzyl isocyanide"], "answer": 3, "solution": "It is carbylamine reaction\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-f90a73c59a920d47.png\"><br>\r\ncarbylamine reaction (test for $1^{\\circ}$ amine)<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7a1bbc6e31f8c13a.png\"><br><img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-81319e65d83b3096.png\">", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300089, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "The order of boiling points of the following compounds is\r\n1. \\(\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\right)_3 \\ddot{\\mathrm{N}}\\)\r\n2. \\(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\ddot{\\mathrm{NH}}_2\\)\r\n3. \\(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\ddot{\\mathrm{N}} \\mathrm{HCH}_3\\)", "options": ["\\(1>3>2\\)", "\\(3>1>2\\)", "\\(2>1>3\\)", "\\(2>3>1\\)"], "answer": 3, "solution": "Like alkanes dominating inter-molecular force for association of amines to its liquid state is van der Waals' force. We know,\r\n\\(\\text {van der Waals' force } \\propto \\frac{1}{\\text { branching of chain }} \\propto \\text { boiling point }\\)\r\nBoiling point\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-0db24720e53c98df.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300090, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "The cyclobutanone of semicarbazone is represented as", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-4c6709f9381f6382.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-bdc12d3e8a9e0d8a.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-941b80c123aa725f.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-99a9332ce8604e04.png\"><br>"], "answer": 1, "solution": "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-5e00fd4d7d0297d6.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300091, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "Identify $X$ and $Y$ in the following reactions\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-4d6ea3cffa4f6cf0.png\"/><br/>", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-3e7be2d2444147d6.png\"/><br/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-2097039055243021.png\"/><br/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-5fd8e9b8468c3ae5.png\"/><br/>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-68850165096c7c70.png\"/><br/>"], "answer": 2, "solution": "(i) On reduction in neutral media, using $\\mathrm{Zn}$ dust and $\\mathrm{NH}_4 \\mathrm{Cl}$ solution nitrobenzene gives phenyl hydroxylamine.\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-377f0a01b0eef624.png\"/><br/>\nWhile in alkaline medium, using $\\mathrm{Zn}-\\mathrm{NaOH}$, mononuclear intermediate products (nitrobenzene and phenylhydroxyl amine) interact to each other to give dinuclear product. Final product using $\\mathrm{Zn}-\\mathrm{NaOH}$ is hydrazobenzene, which in a formed viz the formation of azoxybenzene and azobenzene.<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-42e19a2b61ed3fff.png\"/><br/>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300092, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "The final product C, obtained in this reaction would be<br/> <br/> <img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-fb6f90020d080c07.png\" style=\"width: 287px; height: 116px;\"/>", "options": ["<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-80ec6728ea5125e3.png\" style=\"width: 124px; height: 118px;\"/>", "<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-b8f004ad8c56196c.png\" style=\"width: 90px; height: 122px;\"/>", "<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-94acb2e3e9af9717.png\" style=\"width: 90px; height: 115px;\"/>", "<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-9f626efee633fcf7.png\" style=\"width: 84px; height: 118px;\"/>"], "answer": 3, "solution": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-41d8a6de916a9f59.png\" style=\"width: 434px; height: 120px;\"/>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300093, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "What are the structures of $X, Y$ and $Z$ in the following reaction sequence?\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-4eb717858006ad74.png\"><br>", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-08c1e8b2be40e8e5.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-016f969d21e07dea.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-a49c640ba2412c23.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7847cbaa4a5a3378.png\"><br>"], "answer": 3, "solution": "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-1552efe471ae9680.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300094, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "Identify the structure of $Z$ in the following reaction sequence\r\nPhthalic acid $+\\mathrm{NH}_3 \\rightleftharpoons X \\stackrel{\\Delta}{\\longrightarrow} Y \\underset{\\text { heating }}{\\longrightarrow} Z$", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7e1d1da643f57e8c.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-01e0d5a9a3e73456.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-df662fc359aa4a41.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-bf65f8dc37417ccf.png\"><br>"], "answer": 3, "solution": "The given reaction takes place as follows:\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-c19727169f494844.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300095, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "The compound that forms a yellow oily liquid with nitrous acid is", "options": ["2 -methyl aniline", "methyl amine", "Benzyl amine", "diethyl amine"], "answer": 3, "solution": "Secondary amines (-NH group containing amines), when reacts with nitrous acid $\\left(\\mathrm{HNO}_{2}\\right)$, a yellow oily nitroso compound is formed.\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-449c4032e1ce09d3.png\">", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300096, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "What is $Z$ in the following reaction sequence?\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-4d496b0968fe4071.png\"/><br/>", "options": ["$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{CO}_2 \\mathrm{H}$", "$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{OH}$", "$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{CHO}$", "$\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_6$"], "answer": 2, "solution": "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-e69f1d87e1b1a7a3.png\"/><br/>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300097, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "In the given reaction what is $\\mathrm{X}$ ?\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-3b31ceac0662b6c7.png\"><br>", "options": ["Isonitrile", "Nitrile", "Nitrite", "Oxime"], "answer": 1, "solution": "$$\r\n\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{CN} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{H}_3 \\mathrm{O}^{+}} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{COOH}\r\n$$\r\n        \r\nNitrile\r\n$$\r\n\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{CN} \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii) } \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}]{\\text { (i) } \\mathrm{LiAl} \\mathrm{H}_4} \\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{NH}_2\r\n$$", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300098, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "Reduction of nitrobenzene with $\\mathrm{Zn}$ and alcoholic $\\mathrm{KOH}$ solution results in the formation of the following compound", "options": ["hydrazobenzene", "azobenzene", "aniline", "phenyl hydroxyl amine"], "answer": 0, "solution": "Reduction of nitrobenzene with $\\mathrm{Zn}$ and alcoholic $\\mathrm{KOH}$ results in the formation of hydrazobenzene.\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-9386fd2acb9e175a.png\"/><br/>", "difficulty": "Easy", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300099, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "Which one of the following gives a foul-smelling substance when treated with chloroform and alcoholic $\\mathrm{KOH}$ ?", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-2ce64a4ff085dd3f.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-40aeca5445e41935.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-a8144a0c52a5383f.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-b37220ddcd8cb0aa.png\"><br>"], "answer": 1, "solution": "Aliphatic and aromatic primary amines on heating with chloroform and alcoholic $\\mathrm{KOH}$ form isocyanides or carbylamines which are foul smelling substances. Secondary and tertiary amines do not show this reaction. This reaction is known as carbylamine reaction or isocyanide test. Hence, the compound should be benzylamine.\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-7112248fa5ab1d23.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300100, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "In the following reactions, $P, Q$ and $R$ are\r\n<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-e0a8d094ba4d1974.png\"><br>", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-dc06ba4c60586765.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-42ede7ece344d6b8.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-8fbd860aa8f70ffa.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-04bb5a69820f325f.png\"><br>"], "answer": 1, "solution": "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-8597bc1c2e556368.png\"><br>\r\nIn the above $P, Q$ and $R$ are respectively<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-ee380fa389ffff34.png\"><br>", "difficulty": "Hard", "source": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "_book": "68946f70ebd145663de38728", "_chapterKey": "68946f70ebd145663de38728__689470b46cc631f0fbe63f08__689477a745ed867065047092__6894829b0de8d059acb9a9d9"}, {"id": 300101, "subject": "Chemistry", "chapter": "Amines", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "99 Percentile Qs Bank for JEE Main", "q": "$$\r\n\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{Cl} \\stackrel{\\mathrm{KCN}}{\\longrightarrow} X \\stackrel{\\mathrm{H}_2 / \\text { Catalyst }}{\\longrightarrow} Y \\stackrel{\\mathrm{CHCl}_3}{\\longrightarrow} Z\r\n$$\r\nWhat is ' $Z$ ' in the above sequence of reactions?", "options": ["<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-b1b4ec8ccb9f3868.png\"><br>", "<img src=\"/assets/diagrams/qx-book-acd04cfe60812778.png\"><br>", "<img src=\